.TH "HTMLDIALOGELEMENT.CANCEL_EVENT" "3JS" "January 26, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLDialogElement.cancel_event \- HTMLDialogElement: cancel event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]cancel\f[B]\f[R] event fires on a \f[CR]<dialog>\f[R]
element when the user triggers a close request.
.PP
The \f[CR]cancel\f[R] event handler can be used to override the default
behavior on receiving a close request, and prevent the dialog from
closing.
If the default behavior is not prevented, the dialog will close and fire
a \f[CR]close\f[R] event.
.PP
Close requests might be triggered by:
.IP \(bu 2
Pressing the Esc key on desktop platforms
.IP \(bu 2
Calling the \f[CR]requestClose()\f[R] method
.IP \(bu 2
The back button on mobile platforms
.PP
This event is cancelable and does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqcancel\(dq, (event) => { })

oncancel = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Canceling a dialog
The following example shows a button that, when clicked, opens a
\f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] using the \f[CR]showModal()\f[R] method.
.PP
You can trigger the \f[CR]cancel\f[R] event by either clicking the
\f[I]Request Close\f[R] button to close the dialog (via the
\f[CR]requestClose()\f[R] method) or by pressing the Esc key.
.PP
Note that the \f[CR]cancel\f[R] event handler logs the event and then
returns, allowing the dialog to close (which in turn causes the
\f[CR]close\f[R] event to be emitted).
You can uncomment the line containing \f[CR]event.preventDefault()\f[R]
to cancel the event.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]dialog\f[R] id=\(dqdialog\(dq>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] type=\(dqbutton\(dq id=\(dqrequest\-close\(dq>Request Close</\f[B]button\f[R]>
</\f[B]dialog\f[R]>

<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqopen\(dq>Open dialog</\f[B]button\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dialog = document.getElementById(\(dqdialog\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] openButton = document.getElementById(\(dqopen\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] requestCloseButton = document.getElementById(\(dqrequest\-close\(dq);

\f[I]// Open button opens a modal dialog\f[R]
openButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\(dqopen button click event fired\(dq, \f[B]true\f[R]);
  log(\(dqdialog showModal() called\(dq);
  dialog.showModal();
});

\f[I]// Request close\f[R]
requestCloseButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\(dqrequest close button click event fired\(dq);
  log(\(dqdialog requestClose() called\(dq);
  \f[I]// Triggers the cancel event\f[R]
  dialog.requestClose();
});

\f[I]// Fired when requestClose() is called\f[R]
\f[I]// Prevent the dialog from closing by calling event.preventDefault()\f[R]
dialog.addEventListener(\(dqcancel\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\(dqdialog cancel event fired\(dq);
  \f[I]// Uncomment the next two lines to prevent the dialog from closing\f[R]
  \f[I]// log(\(dqdialog close cancelled\(dq);\f[R]
  \f[I]// event.preventDefault();\f[R]
});

dialog.addEventListener(\(dqclose\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\(dqdialog close event fired\(dq);
});
.EE
.SS Result
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
HTML \f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] element
